value.stringValue: Regardless of the time of day or night, and regardless of the day of the week, speak voice to voice to one of the following three people in order of priority. If the event occurs during non-business hours, the expectation is to reach out via cell as defined below. The call is intended to alert the ISE person of the issue, and to relay relevant information currently available. John Pursell: 602-363-2451 Zack Raves: 602-284-8496 Matt Williams: 623-363-9135 EXAMPLE BELOW: Always leave a detailed voice message if no one picks up providing below example inputs ISE will be required to have Customer Name: Vista Jet Customer Base Location: Malta Aircraft Type: CL350 Aircraft Current Location: Sheremetievo airport, Nothern Moscow region Engine Model: HTF7350 Engine S/N: P136171 Brief Description of Event: a LH Engine Vibration Exceedance CAS MSG. The pilots reported that vibrations and noise were noticed at FL430, followed by an ITT spike on the LH engine. Crew pulled power to idle until close to airport, then commanded shutdown prior to landing. Current Customer Sentiment: Frustrated but under control Known Next Steps: On-going CSM led communications with Vista Jet to coordinate logistics associated with R&R in Russia. Engine will go to Standard Aero Augusta (JSSI Platinum). Timing of Known Next Steps: Unknown at this time. Technical POC: John Pursell (602-363-2451)
CALL ISE Engineering IMMEDIATELY for HTF Engine IFSD’s only
